'3-Fluoromethcathinone', also known as '3-FMC', is a member of the
phenethylamine, amphetamine and cathinone chemical classes. It is a stimulant
drug which is reported to be contained in some legal highs.
3-Fluoroisomethcathinone is produced as a by-product when 3-FMC is synthesised,
the activity of this compound is unknown. [http://www.ltg.uk.net/admin/files/MethCase%282%29.pdf Two cases
of confirmed ingestion of the novel designer compounds: 4-methylmethcathinone
(Mephedrone) and 3-fluoromethcathinone] Susannah Davies et al.
